We recommended to the management to require the Municipal Engineering Office to submit the following documents, as required under the GPPB released “Manual of Procedures for the Procurement of Infrastructure Projects, Volume 3; page 97, to substantiate the asserted time extension due to unfavorable weather condition, otherwise, compute appropriate liquidated damages to be imposed to the contractor without prejudice to the appropriate action/response on the noted slippage:
Copy of written weather report/records from PAGASA to support the unfavourable weather condition asserted;
Copy of duly received written request for extension of completion or construction period from the contractor to the Muncipality of Damulog with written consent of bondsman (Section 10.5, Annex “E” of R.A. 9184 IRR);
Copy of duly approved request for extension duly received by the contractor.

