We have recommended that the management should:
Immediately stop their present system in recording their transactions regarding petty cash and strictly follow the imprest system set forth in Section 48 of NGAs for LGUs;
Require the PCF Disbursing Officer to summarize the petty cash expenses upon the request of replenishment;
Require the PCF Disbursing Officer to immediately conduct reconciliation of the Petty cash book and Petty cash on hand and whenever necessary, make proper entries in the books of accounts;
Ensure that sufficient internal control is in place by requiring quarterly reconciliation of the Petty cash book and petty cash on hand, in compliance with COA Circular No. 97-002.
